article.headline: Austin Peay 82, E. Kentucky 79
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Drake Reed scored 31 points to lead Austin Peay to an 82-79 victory over Eastern Kentucky on Monday night. Reed was 10 of 13 from the floor to help the Governors (7-7, 3-1 Ohio Valley Conference) go 27 of 49 from the field (55.1 percent) and hold off Eastern Kentucky's 13 3-pointers. Reed, who was averaging 19.1 points entering the game, also was 10-for-10 from the free-throw line. Austin Peay led 76-63 with 4:13 remaining in the game, but the Colonels (7-7, 1-3) cut the lead to 81-77 with 14 seconds left before Anthony Campbell hit a free throw to push the advantage to 82-77. Wes Channels added 18 points and Campbell and Kyle Duncan scored 10 points each for the Governors. Eastern Kentucky's Joshua Jones hit five 3-pointers on his way to scoring 20 points. Mike Rose added 15 points and Justin Stommes had 14 points.
